comment:
Guess where Aquaman II is to be filmed?  If you guessed "Queensland" you would be correct.  Maybe the petition to remove AH from the movie will have no effect.  Nevertheless, we Aussies take our biosecurity very seriously.  The Queensland courts may consider it too troublesome to extradite her if she stays away.  If she tries to come back into Australia it will be a different story.

Australia is free of rabies and other canine diseases which are common in the USA.  Bringing the dogs here without proper procedures was bad enough.  Sending them out to a dog grooming salon was beyond the pale.  Her dogs could have spread diseases via Australian dogs coming in contact with their fur, saliva or urine.  Her dangerous, illegal actions and attempts to cover them up by throwing others under the bus, demonstrates just how irresponsible and arrogant this person is.

comment:
Here's the issue Umbrella. Australia has no rabies, foot & mouth, mad cow or bird flu & a lot other nasties. Our island continent has saved us from most of these but the quarantine ensures this situation remains. Australians generally knew this info when I was younger but I don't know if the kids do now. Imagine something getting loose in a land where almost every home has either a dog or a cat or both. We have less than 25 million permanent residents & one of our larger exports other than mining is produce, or beef & lamb & wool. Our beef, sheep & native animal numbers are far higher than human population. None of these animals have immunity to the illnesses animals overseas have.
From the RSPCA's website: "There are over 29 million pets in Australia and we have one of the highest pet ownership rates in the world. Approximately 61% of households in Australia own pets, with dogs being the most common (40%), followed by cats (27%)." I'd suggest their cat numbers are outdated & outback where dogs are used in herding on large stations many of these animals wouldn't be chipped. You call these places ranches btw but a ranch in Australia is a farm. Our cattle & sheep stations are in the hundreds of thousands of acres. Quarantine here is a very serious business.

Fourteen years? One can only hope that the psychopath goes to prison & in Australia. She won't be as pretty when she emerges.

comment:
Just to clarify:
The section where it says the dogs would have to fly in the commercial hold means cargo hold. This isn't an elite concern.
Pets do frequently die when traveling in cargo hold section of the plane. This can be due to shifting cargo, temperature drops that are extreme, stress without anyone even checking on the animals, reduced oxygen in that section of a commercial flight. 
This is NOT an elites only concern. I am a dog breeder and WILL not deliver my puppies to their new families via cargo hold travel. It happens much more frequently than people realize, fatalities of pets traveling in this manner. 
Its an elite issue that she didn't just place her dogs with a kennel or dog sitting service at that point. 

Just wanted to clarify so that even us normal plebs are aware and please never risk your pets life unless any other travel arrangements are impossible and the travel absolutely must happen. It is a huge risk.

comment:
This explanation is from a QLD lawyer from Armstrong Legal.

The offence of perjury consists of deliberately giving false testimony in a judicial proceeding. In Queensland perjury is codified in Section 123 of the Criminal Code 1899. If a person has been lawfully sworn in as a witness and knowingly make a false statement that could affect the result of the proceeding, they can be charged with perjury. This is the case whether the person is an adult or a juvenile. Perjury is a very serious offence as it can undermine the integrity of the judicial system and result in miscarriages of justice. the maximum for perjury is imprisonment for 14 years (Section 124).

comment: Hoo boy, I've been to NZ. They take this stuff seriously. One of those various ways you just REALLY don't want to test the gov on. New Zealand is literally a unique location on the Earth and its law system is heavily centered on conservation. The ten-day quarantine is actually super light considering it's in place for people to recognize parasites and diseases in the animal because they can spread extremely fast unchecked. Most NZ wildlife also has literally no sense of danger owing to a complete lack of predators larger than a spider, and that isn't hyperbole. Snakes? Nonexistent. Wolves? Nope. Big cats/cats at all? Negative. You can quite literally just pick up a kiwi bird at times if you're lucky. Dogs already have a stigma in NZ and taking a ratting dog there is a hard sale out of the gate. To outright ignore the government and the environment, blatantly abuse your own kin, get violent when things don't go your way...Well let's just say I doubt highly Heard'll be invited back to say the least.
